void iField_createGeomDomainFromGeomSet ( const iField_Instance  field_instance,
const iGeom_Instance  geom_instance,
const iBase_EntitySetHandle  set_handle,
iField_DomainHandle *  domain_handle,
int *  err 
)

Create a domain from a set of geometric entities and return its handle.

The entities used as support for distribution functions are iGeom entities in the given iGeom instance, and the entity set is a set of iGeom entities from that instance. The set may be the root set.

Parameters:
field_instance  [in] Field interface instance
geom_instance  [in] iGeom instance to which the set belongs.
set_handle  [in] iGeom entity set containing the entities over which the field is defined.
domain_handle  [out] Handle for the new domain.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)

void iField_createMeshDomainFromGeomEnt ( const iField_Instance  field_instance,
const iGeom_Instance  igeom_instance,
const iBase_EntityHandle  geom_ent_handle,
const iRel_Instance  irel_instance,
const iRel_PairHandle  relation_handle,
iField_DomainHandle *  domain_handle,
int *  err 
)

Create a domain from a geometric entity and return its handle.

The entities used as support for distribution functions are mesh entities in the iMesh instance related to the iGeom instance by the given iRel_PairHandle. The mesh entities are related to the given geometric entity, either directly or through a mesh set related to the geometry entity. The call sequence here is cumbersome, because both the geometric entity and the iRel relation must have instances to go with them. As far as I can tell, iRel can't provide this info currently.

Parameters:
field_instance  [in] Field interface instance
igeom_instance  [in] iGeom instance to which the geometric entity belongs.
geom_ent_handle  [in] iGeom entity to which mesh entities are related.
irel_instance  [in] iRel instance to which the relation belongs.
relation_handle  [in] iRel relation to the mesh entities over which the field is defined.
domain_handle  [out] Handle for the new domain.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)

Create a domain from a set of geometric entities and return its handle.

The entities used as support for distribution functions are mesh entities in the iMesh instance related to the iGeom instance by the given iRel_PairHandle. The mesh entities are related to the geometry entities in the given set of geometry entities, either directly or through mesh sets related to the geometry entities. The call sequence here is cumbersome, because both the geometric entity set and the iRel relation must have instances to go with them. As far as I can tell, iRel can't provide this info currently.

Parameters:
field_instance  [in] Field interface instance
igeom_instance  [in] iGeom instance to which the geometric entity belongs.
geom_set_handle  [in] iGeom entity set to which mesh entities are related.
irel_instance  [in] iRel instance to which the relation belongs.
relation_handle  [in] iRel relation to the mesh entities over which the field is defined.
domain_handle  [out] Handle for the new domain.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)

void iField_destroyDomain ( const iField_Instance  instance,
iField_DomainHandle  handle,
int *  err 
)

Destroy a domain.

This should refuse to destroy if the domain is in use. This only destroys the Domain, without affecting the underlying mesh entities, or any possible mesh sets, geom ents, or geom sets.

Parameters:
instance  [in] iField instance handle
handle  [in] Domain to destroy.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)

void iField_getDomainMeshSet ( const iField_Instance  field_instance,
const iField_DomainHandle  domain_handle,
iBase_EntitySetHandle *  mesh_set_handle,
int *  err 
)

Which mesh set contains entities supporting this field?

This function will return an error if the domain was created using createGeomDomainFromGeomSet or createMeshDomainFromGeomSet. If createMeshDomainFromGeomEnt was used, then an error is returned if the iGeom entity was associated directly to multiple mesh entities rather than to an iMesh set of entities. In any event, if the function returns iBase_SUCCESS, the set handle must be the one which contains exactly the entities in the domain.

Parameters:
field_instance  [in] Field interface instance.
domain_handle  [in] Domain being queried.
mesh_set_handle  [out] Mesh set to which mesh entities belong.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)
